      "content": "\"letting go of the effort\"... that sounds nice in theory but it feels so final. it's like i've spent years trying to patch the cracks but the whole foundation is just gone. if someone is truly, fundamentally broken, isn't trying to keep going just a way of prolonging the inevitable? it feels less like \"healing\" and more like trying to perform CPR on a ghost.",
